- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is likely because the paper deals with pushdown automata and their probabilistic extensions, which are classic topics in automata theory. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is possible because the paper presents a general construction for reducing bisimilarity of probabilistic transition systems to non-deterministic ones, which involves algorithmic techniques. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is possible because the paper establishes complexity bounds for bisimilarity of various subclasses of probabilistic pushdown automata, which is a central topic in computational complexity theory.
